<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="8" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="9.[192,1440,1840,1928]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,347,1840,1864]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species is named for our friend Robert Perger (
<collectingRegion box="[979,1269,1840,1865]" country="Bolivia" name="Santa Cruz" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Santa Cruz de la Sierra</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1281,1371,1840,1864]" name="Bolivia" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
), who collected part of the 
<typeStatus box="[435,488,1873,1897]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">type</typeStatus>
series, for his spirit of collaboration and contributions to the study of Neotropi- cal longhorned beetles. The epithet is a noun in the genitive case.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
